==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monocotyledones
<hw>Monocotyledones</hw></mhw> <pos>prop.
n.</pos> <def>A class of plants comprising seed plants that produce an
embryo with a single cotyledon and parallel-veined leaves: grasses;
lilies; palms; and orchids. It is divided into four subclasses or
superorders: Alismatidae; Arecidae; Commelinidae; and
Liliidae.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> class <class>Monocotyledones</class>,
<class>Monocotyledonae</class>, class <class>Monocotyledonae</class>,
<class>Liliopsida</class>, class <class>Liliopsida</class>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monocotyledonous</ent>⟦br⟧
